---
description: Enforce dependency direction and layer ownership in apps and libraries
globs: "{apps,libs}/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- `libs/domain` must remain pure TypeScript and must not import NestJS, Drizzle, PostgreSQL, Redis, BullMQ, HTTP or provider SDKs.
- `libs/application` may depend on Domain and Contracts, but must not import concrete Infrastructure implementations.
- Application must not import `@nestjs/*`; register use cases via composition-root factory providers.
- `libs/contracts` owns ports, tokens and provider-neutral boundary data.
- `libs/infrastructure` implements Contracts and must not leak provider-specific types into Domain or Application.
- Controllers, guards, workers, cron schedules and migration bootstraps are interface/composition code and must not contain business rules.
- Register concrete implementations against tokens in composition modules.
- When changing a token or port, search and update every provider, export, import and consumer before verification.
